Monica Iheakam Super Eagles’ Captain, Mikel Obi said his team hopes to storm the Russia 2018 World Cup with a winning mentality and will not underrate the Simba of DR of Congo. Eagles will face their African rivals in a send-off friendly at the Adokiye Amiesimaka Stadium in Port Harcourt this evening. “We do not expect the Congolese to be easy opposition,” Mikel was quoted in a Nigeria Football Federation press release on Sunday. “They have a strong team made up of talented players and we know this is good opposition for us to confront before going to the World Cup. “The FIFA World Cup is no picnic. We have to arrive in Russia with a winning mentality and you get that feeling of being ready only after beating strong teams.” DR Congo, with 28 players landed in Port Harcourt last Thursday, boasting they were in Nigeria to give the Super Eagles a good match and Mikel is up for a tough duel. Coach Gernot Rohr had already revealed that five players would be cut from the provisional list of 30 after Monday’s encounter, leaving him with only two more to drop, when announcing the final squad in Bad Tatzmannsdorf, Austria next Monday.